				Doesn't matter, most people who get the patents aren't the orginal designers to begin with. The problem is that most people who invent it like to invent and don't care about patents. 
<br />

<br />
Good is example is Alexander Graham Bell, he invented the telephone, just a month after someone else did. The thing is the original inventer, who's name escapes me at the moment, didn't rush it to the patent office like Bell did, so when he sent to have it patented it was moments after Bell's had arrived at the office and so they gave it to Bell. There's quite a bit of that so eh, screw patents.<br />
