<br />

<br />
The proliferation of open licenses are using the rules of the closed licenses to defeat them. The GPL is the best example of this in action. I strongly suspect that as open licenses become more common and accepted, you'll see the open products crushing the competition, unltil quite literally there is nothing left on the playing field except for the lone open solution. Monopoly by quality, and a form of competition that cannot be stopped or killed or strangled at a revenue stream or bought out... it's inevitable, really. That would be an Orwellian nightmare, except that the rules of the open solution allow anyone to use it for anything, so the tyrrany is one of freedom rather than control. It puts the users in charge and puts the abusers out of business. Seeing that kind of simple solution arise out of such a pile of wanton chaos and malice using its own rules to defeat it is almost enough to make me believe that some god somewhere knows what he is doing...
<br />

<br />
You want to know how these pointless artifical walls hold us back? Put your brain in what if mode for a moment and pull a John Lennon. Imagine what it would be like if the free use of all ideas and information was allowed, and the sum total of humanity's knowledge was at the fingertips of every living person. Add to that the sum total of every meaningful bit of artwork for inspiration and what do you get?
<br />

<br />
And please don't tell me you are foolish enough to think that nobody will create, research, or think for themselves in that society. In that society, the only things of value will be new ideas, new creations, and original thought. How people get paid is a petty secondary concern that will work itself out long after the walls come down.
<br />

<br />
If you want to know the end result, here is the long view.
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://www.ugcs.caltech.edu/~phoenix/vinge/vinge-sing.html" target="_blank">http://www.ugcs.caltech.edu/~phoenix/vinge/vinge-sing.html</a>
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://www.kurzweilai.net/articles/art0134.html?printable=1" target="_blank">http://www.kurzweilai.net/articles/art0134.html?printable=1</a><br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
