				I dont need to imagine.  Someone else already did:
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />
A spectre is haunting Europe -- the spectre of communism. All the powers of old Europe have entered into a holy alliance to exorcise this spectre: Pope and Tsar, Metternich and Guizot, French Radicals and German police-spies, [Coca-Cola, Mc Donalds, IBM and Microsoft].
<br />

<br />
...
<br />

<br />
The history of all hitherto existing society [2] is the history of class struggles. 
<br />

<br />
Freeman and slave, patrician and plebian, lord and serf, guild-master [3] and journeyman, in a word, oppressor and oppressed, stood in constant opposition to one another, carried on an uninterrupted, now hidden, now open fight, a fight that each time ended, either in a revolutionary reconstitution of society at large, or in the common ruin of the contending classes. 
<br />

<br />
In the earlier epochs of history, we find almost everywhere a complicated arrangement of society into various orders, a manifold gradation of social rank. In ancient Rome we have patricians, knights, plebians, slaves; in the Middle Ages, feudal lords, vassals, guild-masters, journeymen, apprentices, serfs; in almost all of these classes, again, subordinate gradations. 
<br />

<br />
The modern bourgeois society that has sprouted from the ruins of feudal society has not done away with class antagonisms. It has but established new classes, new conditions of oppression, new forms of struggle in place of the old ones.
<br />

<br />
-Karl Marx and Frederick Engels</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Look, I hate to burst your bubble but the concept is not new.  The market wins in the end because it is a natural force of human interaction, not because it is a repressive construct of evil corporations.  Just like pecking order exists as a natural force in human interaction.  You can shape it with culture but if you try to erase it
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">@#%$. This link proves you dead wrong. Read any of them.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
No, it doesn't it proves the patent office allows some silly @#%$.  however the patent office is only a REGISTRAR. It sorts the best that it can with the resources it has and if there is a contention between people over the patent, then the court decides.
<br />

<br />
So, it is not the patent office that is the devil.  Its just underfunded.  If there is any basis in what you are saying you need to point to patent law and judicial ruling for how it is interpretted.  Someone elses rant (and your link goes to someone who says that what he is writing is a rant) is not evidence.
<br />

<br />
Show me that patents are not temporary and do not have to be produced on in order to be maintained for a long period of time.  There is allowance for having time to make it marketable but you have to produce an example of it working. No?
<br />

<br />
###
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">you'll see the open products crushing the competition, unltil quite literally there is nothing left on the playing field except for the lone open solution. Monopoly by quality, and a form of competition that cannot be stopped or killed or strangled at a revenue stream or bought out... it's inevitable, really.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
You will see more and more programmers stop working on programming and start working at steer manuer shoveling as the lack of payment for their creative work drives them to other things in order to feed their families, keep rain off their heads, get an education, etc... etc.. etc...
<br />

<br />
Look at the Linux distributions. They have added non open source pieces to linux to make it suitable to enterprise.  There are no real distributions that set up easily and cleanly, because that is where the profit is in support.  As time goes on the distributions will design themselves into more support reliant configurations and less and less of the actual distribution or stitching it together will be open source.  The core will be open source but in time as charity dwindles and "feeding the kids" becomes more important to people it will happen more.
<br />

<br />
Madrake is "now a profitable company."
<br />

<br />
Check out the prices for enterprise ready configurations for Red Hat.
<br />

<br />
SuSe will not let you DL installation ISOs you either have to connect to their server for install or gank all 6 gig (or just the portions you want if you can spend 30 man hours sorting through the packages).
<br />

<br />
I thank god for open source because it does provide a minimum bar of standard that has raised the bar on Microsoft and forced that unnatural monopoly to get on the ball or die.  It may die and that is the natural order of the market.
<br />

<br />
If it is smart Microsoft will just adopt Some flavor of open source as its own kernal one day and say thanks as it continues on with making interfaces for it with its vast ability to PAY developers to do it.  If it doesnt it will die, but that will not be the end of innovation nor of a profit based market.  It will simply be a shift in the order of things and into the hands of other innovators that will expect reward for their labor.
<br />

<br />
Open source is a holy rite of charity from man to man.  It should be revered as such and supported as such. Just like communism, its a great rallying cry but it is not a long term solution to patents. You cannot try and push it into somethign that is not freely participated in by the free will of men.
<br />

<br />
Just like communism it has this myth surrounding it that it will end patents (compare class struggle) period and is a tool to bring down the giant corprations which is absurd. It is a natural shift in the market in response to a monopoly that tried to bully the market. The strength of the people is felt in retaliation through banding together agaisnt a monster, however once the dragon is dead or subdued, the knight that champions the people must go home to his farm, or become a dragon himself.
<br />

<br />
Be careful of an unconsidered following of these neo-marxist idiots that are spouting rhetoric they are dientifying a phenomenon that is as old as trade, and callin it new. If you are not VERY careful you may find yourself commiting genocide or worse in the name of GPL or some other icon of the day.
<br />

<br />
After all who would have imagined that a man like Trotsky would spearhead a revolution in the name of oppresseed masses and then turn around and not even live to see it used to murder millions upon million upon millions.
<br />

<br />
It is not open source that is the danger.  Just like it was not communism as an idea nor in voluntary practice that was dangerous.  It was fools that tried to make it what it could never be that destroyed communism and turned mans want to do charity to his fellow man upside down on itself. Tthe same will be true with open source if this sort of non-sense diatribe is waved as its banner.<br />
