				</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"> I dont need to imagine. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
That's one of the dumbest things I've heard a person say. Surely you can do better than thumping on a bunch of old textbooks (that are admittedly full of good ideas) and saying, "Because these men thought once upon a time I don't have to!"
<br />

<br />
It is new, and I'll tell you why: There is no Lord in control of these open technologies. If every reconstruction results in a Lord-Serf relationship, yet here we see a system that has designed the Lord out completely, how is that not new? One can indeed be influential with these new technologies, but only by contributing to them and making them stronger, and playing by their rules. This influence does not give you control. There is no Lord. You are looking at a newer, better incarnation of old ideas with a fundamental design change.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"> Show me that patents are not temporary and do not have to be produced on in order to be maintained for a long period of time. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Easy: <a href="http://www.gnu.org/philosophy/amazonpatent.html" target="_blank">http://www.gnu.org/philosophy/amazonpatent.html</a>
<br />

<br />
If you're going to continue this line of arguing define "temporary" and what constitutes "product". This patent represents neither in my book.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"> No, it doesn't it proves the patent office allows some silly @#%$. however the patent office is only a REGISTRAR. It sorts the best that it can with the resources it has and if there is a contention between people over the patent, then the court decides. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
