<br />

<br />
<a href="http://www.ladas.com/Patents/USPatentHistory.html" target="_blank" class="postlink">US Patent History</a>
<br />

<br />
If you need a basic refresher.  The USCode and case law can be researched here:
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
###
<br />

<br />
I maintain that patents will not be killed by public license but rather be improved by it.
<br />

<br />
You complain that Amazon owns a patent for a shopping cart system? Know what, thats exactly what they own, and they buit a chunk of economy doing it.  They took an idea and bloomed it into a massive company that proovided a basic service and was an archetype for internet commerce.
<br />

<br />
Whats wrong with that?
<br />

<br />
###
<br />

<br />
Question for the lawyers:
<br />

<br />
If Amazon thinks that you are infringing on their patent, who is the burden of proof on?<br />
